{
  "id": "bonne-presse-catechism-in-pictures",
  "name": {
    "fr-FR": "Catéchisme en Images",
    "en-US": "The Catechism in Pictures",
    "pt-BR": "Catecismo Ilustrado"
  },
  "author": {
    "fr-FR": "Maison de la Bonne Presse",
    "en-US": "Maison de la Bonne Presse (trans. E. E. Fernandez)",
    "pt-BR": "Maison de la Bonne Presse"
  },
  "description": {
    "fr-FR": "Un catéchisme illustré classique en soixante-huit tableaux, présentant la doctrine chrétienne par l'image et un texte explicatif court. Composé sous le pontificat de saint Pie X et publié à Paris par la Maison de la Bonne Presse, il expose le Symbole des Apôtres, les Sacrements, les Commandements de Dieu et de l'Église, la Prière, les Fins dernières, les Péchés capitaux, les Vertus et les Œuvres de miséricorde — chaque tableau étant accompagné d'une « explication » qui en commente les détails iconographiques.",
    "en-US": "A classic illustrated catechism in sixty-eight plates, presenting Christian doctrine through image and a short explanatory text. Composed under the pontificate of St. Pius X and published in Paris by the Maison de la Bonne Presse, it expounds the Apostles' Creed, the Sacraments, the Commandments of God and of the Church, Prayer, the Last Things, the Capital Sins, the Virtues, and the Works of Mercy — each plate accompanied by an « Explanation » that comments on its iconographic details.",
    "pt-BR": "Um catecismo ilustrado clássico em sessenta e oito gravuras, apresentando a doutrina cristã pela imagem e por um breve texto explicativo. Composto sob o pontificado de São Pio X e publicado em Paris pela Maison de la Bonne Presse, expõe o Símbolo dos Apóstolos, os Sacramentos, os Mandamentos de Deus e da Igreja, a Oração, os Novíssimos, os Pecados capitais, as Virtudes e as Obras de Misericórdia — cada gravura acompanhada por uma « Explicação » que comenta os seus detalhes iconográficos."
  },
  "composed": 1908,
  "languages": [
    "fr-FR",
    "en-US",
    "pt-BR"
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "language": "fr-FR",
      "url": "https://missiondesainteanne.wordpress.com/cat-4a/",
      "description": "Original French edition (Paris, Maison de la Bonne Presse, 1908). Scanned reproduction with embedded OCR text layer, hosted by missiondesainteanne.wordpress.com and lafrancechretienne.wordpress.com. Public domain (Imprimatur Parisiis 14 octobris 1912)."
    },
    {
      "language": "en-US",
      "url": "https://missiondesainteanne.wordpress.com/cat-4a/",
      "description": "English translation by E. E. Fernandez (Paris, Maison de la Bonne Presse, 1912; reprinted 1938). Sixty-eight full-page illustrations alternating with and facing text. Public domain (Imprimatur Southwarci 27 junii 1912)."
    },
    {
      "language": "pt-BR",
      "url": "internal:fr-FR",
      "description": "Brazilian Portuguese translation rendered from the French canonical (1908) via the project's translate-book skill, in modern post-1971 orthography. The 1910 Lisbon edition (Catecismo Illustrado) was consulted as a reference but not used as the source due to pre-1911 European orthography that would require extensive modernization."
    }
  ],
